                  "display": "Information"
                }
              ]
            },
            "valueString": "Patient is a 52-year-old male presenting with chronic low back pain and right-sided radiculopathy. Symptoms began 10 weeks ago after lifting injury. Pain radiates from lower back to right posterior thigh and calf. Pain rated 7/10 on VAS. Positive straight leg raise test at 40 degrees on the right. Decreased ankle jerk reflex on the right. No bowel or bladder dysfunction."
          },
          {
            "sequence": 2,
            "category": {
              "coding": [
                {
                  "system": "http://terminology.hl7.org/CodeSystem/claiminformationcategory",
                  "code": "info",
                  "display": "Information"
                }
              ]
            },
            "valueString": "Conservative treatment history: Physical therapy x 12 sessions over 8 weeks (McKenzie method, core stabilization) — minimal improvement. NSAIDs (naproxen 500mg BID) x 6 weeks — partial relief. Oral prednisone taper (Medrol dose pack) — temporary improvement only. Home exercise program compliant. Failed conservative treatment per ACR Appropriateness Criteria."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
